The regression specification I will employ first is as follows:

\[Y_{st} = \alpha + \beta * TREAT_s + \gamma * POST_t + \delta_{rDD}*(TREAT_s \times POST_t) + \epsilon_{st}\]
In addition, I can also use year (\(\phi_t\)) and sector (\(\sigma_s\)) fixed effects to estimate the DiD estimate:

\[Y_{st} = \alpha + \delta_{rDD}*(TREAT_s \times POST_t) + \sigma_s + \phi_t + e_{st}\]

Lastly, I will confirm my Difference-in-Differences estimate results from the regression specification and complement it with a set of visualizations of DiD in action.
